<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="18">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Bankeraceae" genus="Boletopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Boletopsis nothofagi" order="Thelephorales" pageId="5" pageNumber="18" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="nothofagi">Boletopsis nothofagi</taxonomicName>
differs from described species in the more elongate spores with a narrow central waist, granular extra-cellular material becoming green in KOH and habitat in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nothofagaceae" genus="Nothofagus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Nothofagus" order="Fagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Nothofagus</taxonomicName>
forests (
<bibRefCitation author="Niemala, T" journalOrPublisher="Karstenia" pageId="5" pageNumber="18" pagination="12 - 28" title="On Fennoscandian polypores 10. Boletopsis leucomelaena and B. grisea described and llustrated." volume="29" year="1989">Niemala and Saarenoska 1989</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Harrison, K" journalOrPublisher="Beihefte Nova Hedwigia" pageId="5" pageNumber="18" pagination="119 - 121" title="A New Species of Boletopsis." volume="51" year="1975">Harrison 1975</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Watling, R" journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of Scotland" pageId="5" pageNumber="18" pagination="81 - 92" title="A new species of Boletopsis associated with Pinus sylvestris L in Scotland." url="10.1080/03746600608685110" volume="58" year="2006">Watling and Milne 2006</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
